to be one step? Why can't distro packagers take care of build-and-run?  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here's a few more though.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Documented build-run-tests-upload-release. (Maybe this is why you need
build-and-run-tests? I still disagree that it absolutely must be one
step.)  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Documented release announcement procedure. (Unlikely to get this down
to one step though because there are many places to announce a project,
not all of them belong to you.) Basically, &lt;a href="http://wiki.goonmill.org/HowtoReleaseHypy"&gt;this
document&lt;/a&gt;.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
